# Authorization

- Separate authentication (who) from authorization (what they can do).
- Check permissions at the API/service layer, not only in UI.
- Prefer RBAC for most apps; ABAC when fine-grained policy rules are required.
- Default deny: explicitly grant permissions, never assume access.
- Validate resource ownership on every read/write (IDOR prevention).
- Never trust client-side role checks alone.
- Centralize policy logic; avoid scattered `if user.is_admin` checks across codebase.
- Log authorization failures for security monitoring.
- Scope API keys and service accounts to minimum required permissions.
- Test authorization with multiple role fixtures in integration tests.
